==Arabic==
===Verb I===
'''{{ARchar|فجر}}''' (fájara)

# to [[cleave]], to [[break]] up, to [[dig]] up
# to act immorally, to [[sin]]
# to commit [[adultery]]

===Verb II===
'''{{ARchar|فجّر}}''' (fájjara)

# to create an outlet or passage (for water)
# to let pour forth
# to [[cleave]], to [[split]]
# to [[explode]]

===Verb IV===
'''{{ARchar|[[افجر|أفجر]]}}''' (’áfjara)

# to commit [[adultery]]

===Verb V===
'''{{ARchar|[[تفجر|تفجّر]]}}''' (tafájjara)

# to [[gush]] out, to [[spurt]] forth
# to [[break]] out, to [[erupt]], to [[burst]] out

===Verb VII===
'''{{ARchar|[[انفجر]]}}''' (infájara)

# to go off, to [[discharge]], to [[burst]]
# to [[burst]] forth
# to [[explode]], to [[detonate]]
# to [[overflow]]
# to [[swoop]] down

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|فجر}}''' (fajr) {{m}}

# [[dawn]], [[daybreak]]
#''(figurative)'' [[dawn]], [[beginning]], [[outset]], [[start]]

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|فجر}}''' (fajr) {{f}}

# the morning [[prayer]]

